# View Pane & Modifier Clicks

## View Pane (Main Content Area)

- The main content area (view pane) can be **split into multiple panes** or shown as **tabs** (DESIGN.md: "Content (tab-based)").
- Anything that can be "opened" in the view pane (e.g. a note, a task, an entity) must support **two modifier-click actions** in addition to normal click.

## Modifier-Click Requirements

**Every openable item (notes, tasks, entities, search results, etc.) must:**

1. **Normal click** — Open in the **current** pane (replace or focus existing content).
2. **Shift-click** — Open in a **new pane to the right** (split view). The new pane is created and the item opens there.
3. **Cmd-click (Mac) / Ctrl-click (Windows)** — Open in a **new tab**. The tab is added and the item opens in that tab.

Implement this by:

- Handling `onClick` with `event.shiftKey` and `event.metaKey` (use `event.ctrlKey` on Windows if needed for Ctrl-click).
- Calling the appropriate callback: `onOpenInNewPane?.(item)` or `onOpenInNewTab?.(item)` when the modifier is set; otherwise perform the default open-in-current-pane behavior.
- Providing these callbacks from the view-pane/shell layer to list and tree components that render openable items.

## Consistency

- Do not add openable items (links, list rows, tree nodes, search result rows) without implementing modifier-click support.
- Use a shared pattern or hook (e.g. `useOpenableItem({ onSelect, onOpenInNewPane, onOpenInNewTab })`) so behavior is consistent across the app.
